<item>
            <title>[LU-19590] Supp gid fix for cross-MDT operations where parent/child on diff MDTs w/ different groups</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19590</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For cross-MDT open where parent and child are on different MDTs and owned by different supplementary groups, we should hint client via similar mechanism as in &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56098&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56098&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now, for cross-MDT open, mdt_reint_open calls mdt_cross_open which skips the logic later to check for EACESS and hint client. The client will try and guess the child dir or file&apos;s permissions w/ the parent&apos;s permissions - if they do not match, client will get an incorrect EACESS. We can fix this by adding a check for EACESS into mdt_cross_open.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modified existing sanity-sec 83 to fail w/o this change&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
